30/07/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police arrested Fatmir Arifi, suspected member of a key organised crime group in the Balkans, on Wednesday (July 29th) near Belgrade. 
Arifi was arrested as part of an operation against the illegal trafficking of Albanian citizens into EU countries. 
His alleged task within the organisation, headed by Delal Sulejmani, was to meet illegal immigrants in the Kosovo region of Gnjilane, and transfer them to Belgrade. 
In the Serbian capital, they were to be handed off to other members of the group. 
Arifi was arrested near Belgrade without any personal ID documents. 
(B92, BTA, RTS - 29/07/09)
